100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 18, 1925, international tensions simmered as the League of Nations continued discussions on disarmament, reflecting a global desire for peace in the wake of World War I. In the United States, President Calvin Coolidge addressed the nation, emphasizing the importance of economic stability and growth. Meanwhile, in Germany, the political landscape remained volatile, with increasing unrest and calls for reform amid economic struggles.
